# Scenario: MARGINAL SIGNAL — u-blox SARA-R412M, customer reports "device connects
# sometimes, drops other times. Logs say everything is fine when it works."
# Key signals:
#   +CSQ: 5,99               (RSSI ~ -103 dBm — bottom of usable range)
#   +UCGED reports RSRP -118 dBm, RSRQ -17.5 dB — both at LTE-M sensitivity edge
#   +CEREG: 0,1              (currently registered, but unstable)
#   +UPING shows mixed: some replies at ~2000 ms RTT, two timeouts in 4 packets
# Diagnosis: classic "edge of coverage" intermittent connectivity. Device is not
# broken — it's at the RF cliff where small environmental changes (door closed,
# truck parked nearby, weather) push it over the edge.
# Customer guidance:
#   - Improve antenna: ensure it is OUTSIDE any metal enclosure (Faraday cage).
#   - Reposition: even 30 cm of vertical change can swing RSRP by 6+ dB.
#   - Consider higher-gain external antenna with proper SMA/u.FL connection.
#   - For permanent low-coverage sites, evaluate switching to NB-IoT (better link
#     budget at the cost of throughput) — Hologram supports both Cat-M1 and NB1.
# Triage tip: if RSRP > -110 and RSRQ > -15 the link should be solid. The "between
# -110 and -120" zone is where most "intermittent" tickets actually live.

AT+CPIN?
+CPIN: READY
OK
AT+CFUN=1
OK
AT+CSQ
+CSQ: 5,99
OK
AT+UCGED=5
+RSRP: 1,2850,"-118.00"
+RSRQ: 1,2850,"-17.50"
+CESQ: 99,99,255,255,30,7
OK
AT+CEREG?
+CEREG: 0,1
OK
AT+CGATT?
+CGATT: 1
OK
AT+CGACT=1,1
OK
AT+UPING="8.8.8.8"
OK
+UUPING: 1,32,"8.8.8.8","8.8.8.8",242,1980
+UUPINGER: 2,"Timeout"
+UUPINGER: 3,"Timeout"
+UUPING: 4,32,"8.8.8.8","8.8.8.8",242,2210
